  protein: 36 g
---

Peel and finely dice the @garlic clove{2}. Peel the @ginger{1} using the edge of a
#spoon{} and very finely chop (or grate). Chop the @spring onion{2} into
micro-thin discs, separating the white and green parts.

Mix together the @soy sauce{1.5%tbsp} with 1 tbsp of @?sugar{} and the
@sesame oil{1/2%tbsp}. Add half the garlic and half the ginger and keep stirring
until the sugar dissolves. Next stir in the whites of the spring onions.

Pour the mixture over the @British beef mince{250%g}, mix thoroughly and leave
for as long as possible.

> This would be a great step to do well in advance - we left it for an hour and
> it made a HUGE difference to the flavour, but let your appetite make the
> decision!

Boil a medium-sized #pot{} of water with @salt{1/4%tsp}. Once the water comes to
a rapid boil add in the @Tenderstem® broccoli{1}. Bring back to the boil and
leave for ~{1%minute}. Lift the broccoli from the water and keep to the side -
don't throw the water away!

Pour out all but about 350ml of the boiling water. Place your
@basmati rice{} into this 350ml of boiling water and put a #lid{} on. Cook for
~{10%minutes} on the lowest heat possible then remove from the heat for
~{10%minutes}. Do not touch the lid until 20 mins are up to ensure the rice is
cooked perfectly.

Heat @oil{1%tsp} on high heat in a #frying pan{}. Once really hot add in your
beef bulgogi mix and fry for around ~{4-5%minutes} until cooked.

> Patrick slightly undercooked his to keep it really juicy.

> If you only have a small pan don't overcrowd it - cook the beef in batches to
> brown it off.

Once the beef is cooked remove it from the pan and keep it warm. Drain some of
the oil from the beef into the pan and get it really hot. Throw in the
remaining garlic and ginger then after ~{15%seconds} add in the broccoli. Cook
for ~{2%minutes} - you want it to be a little crunchy when you eat it.

Separate the grains of rice with a #fork{} and stir through the greens of the
spring onion. Serve the bulgogi beef with the rice, the broccoli on the side and
a sprinkling of @sesame seeds{1/2%tsp} on top.